      "title": "ℹ️ About — BrainDead Mask Tools",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "# 🧠 BrainDead — Mask Tools\n\nFour standalone mask utility nodes for common image prep tasks.\n\n## BD_LuminanceMask\nExtracts the **brightest** and **darkest** regions of an image as masks.\n- **top_percent** — top N% of pixels by brightness → highlight mask\n- **bottom_percent** — bottom N% → shadow mask\n- **soft_edge** — feather the threshold boundary\n- **gradient_mode** — output a smooth gradient instead of a binary threshold\n- **exclude_above / exclude_below** — clip pure whites/blacks from the selection (avoids blown highlights or crushed blacks)\n\n**Use when:** Generating shadow/highlight masks for lighting adjustments, PBR bake inputs, or selective color grading.\n\n## BD_MaskFlatten\nComposites a masked image onto a solid color or another image.\n- **flatten_mode: alpha_composite** — standard alpha blend over background\n- **flatten_mode: grayscale** — convert result to greyscale\n- **flatten_mode: image_to_red / green / blue** — paste luminance into a single colour channel\n- **background_color** — preset backgrounds: white, black, checker, magenta, custom hex\n- **mask_threshold** — binarise the mask at this value before flatten\n\n**Use when:** Preparing a no-BG character for 3D pipelines, creating a flat-shaded skin layer, or previewing a mask against a clean background.\n\n## BD_CropToMask\nCrops an image to the bounding box of its mask content.\n- **padding_pct** — adds a percentage of extra space around the crop (0.15 = 15%)\n- **fixed_size_px** — ignore bounding box, use a fixed crop size centred on the mask\n- **square** — force a square crop\n- **output_size** — resize the crop to this final size\n- **resize_mode: fit** — letterbox to output_size; **stretch** — fill exactly\n- **channel** — which image channel to use as the mask signal (R, G, B, A, all)\n\n**Use when:** Extracting a face/object from a segmentation mask, preparing square inputs for diffusion models, or isolating a subject.\n\n## BD_FillMaskHoles\nFills interior holes in a binary mask.\n- **closing_radius** — morphological closing (dilate + erode) to seal near-touching boundary gaps before fill\n- **smooth_edges** — Gaussian blur on the output for soft feathering\n\n**Use when:** SAM3 detected the subject perimeter but left internal gaps (mouth interior, eye whites, clothing texture holes). Run before BD_PackChannels or BD_RemoveBackground.\n\n---\n**BrainDeadGuild** — created by **BizaNator**\n[BrainDeadGuild.com](https://BrainDeadGuild.com) · [BrainDead.TV](https://BrainDead.TV) · [GitHub](https://github.com/BizaNator/ComfyUI-BrainDead) · [Discord](https://braindeadguild.com/discord)\n"
      ]
    },
